flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: New product introduction (NPI) announcement.]
  A --> N1[Stream: DDM/Crawlers - Ingest pre-orders and reservations data.]
  N1 --> N2[Cortex: Cortex Auto Forecast - Analyze pre-orders and reservations using Cortex Auto Forecast.]
  N2 --> N3[Cortex: Cortex Auto Forecast - Simulate demand for early production builds and pilot programs.]
  N3 --> N4[Cortex: Cortex Auto Forecast - Project ramp-up volumes and sales for new model launches.]
  N4 --> N5[Cortex: Cortex Auto Forecast - Forecast demand for specific vehicle features and trims.]
  N5 --> N6{PB: CWB Lifecycle - Present recommendations for production and supplier adjustments.}
  N6 -->|Primary| P1[Action: Automate adjustments to production, supplier replenishment, and capacity planning based on forecasted demand.]
  P1 --> Z1[Outcome: Reduced working capital tied to NPI stock, improved launch OTIF, and better alignment of supplier and plant capacities with market reception.]
  N6 -->|Market interest is lower than expected.| B1[Adjust production ramp-up and supplier orders accordingly.]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Reduced inventory risk and optimized production capacity.]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N6 -->|Market interest is higher than expected.| B2[Accelerate production ramp-up and increase supplier orders.]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Meet increased demand and avoid stockouts.]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N6 -->|Feature/trim level demand is uneven.| B3[Adjust production mix to align with dealer demand.]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Optimize revenue and minimize inventory risk.]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]